.tmux.conf to change settings
    # Change the prefix key
    set-option -g prefix C-j
    unbind-key C-b
    bind-key C-j send-prefix
 
    # Status line color
    set -g status-style fg=white,bold
    #set -ag status-style bg=magenta
    # Highlight active window
    set-window-option -g window-status-current-bg red
 
    # Automatically set window title
    setw -g automatic-rename on
 
    # Use v to trigger selection
    bind-key -T copy-mode-vi v send-keys -X begin-selection
 
    # Useful stuff from Solomon White in comments about 45% down the page
    # https://blog.hawkhost.com/2010/07/02/tmux-%e2%80%93-the-terminal-multiplexer-part-2/#modifying-tab-color
    # use "v" and "s" to do vertical/horizontal splits, like vim
    bind s split-window -v
    bind v split-window -h
    # use the vim motion keys to move between panes
    bind h select-pane -L
    bind j select-pane -D
    bind k select-pane -U
    bind l select-pane -R
    # use vim motion keys while in copy mode
    setw -g mode-keys vi
Reload config
    Put following into your config so you can reload while working in tmux:
        unbind r
        bind-key r source-file ~/.tmux.conf \; \
            display-message "Reload source-file: done"
Help:  ?
Sessions
    s       List sessions
    $       Rename current session
    New session
        tmux new -s session-name        
        Using a name lets you reattach more easily
    Attach
        tmux attach -t 0
        tmux attach -t session-name
    Detach
        d
        tmux detach
    List sessions
        tmux ls
    Kill session
        tmux kill-session -t session-name
Command mode
    :       Switch to command mode
    <ret>   Exit command mode with no text
    : new-window -n name
Windows
    c       Create new
    ,       Rename current
    w       List
    %       Split horizontally
    "       Split vertically
    l       Last used window
    n       Next window
    p       Previous window
    0 to 9  Windows 0 through 9
Panes
    <spc>   Cycle between layouts
    %       Horizontal pane
    "       Vertical pane
    h       Move to left pane
    j       Move to pane below
    l       Move to right pane
    k       Move to pane above
    q       Show pane numbers
    o       Toggle between panes
    }       Swap with next pane
    {       Swap with previous pane
    !       Break the pane out of the window
    x       Kill the current pane
    z       Toggle current pane to full screen

Copy mode
    <prefix>[
    Use vi keys to move around on screen
    Press spacebar to start selecting text
    Hit enter key to copy to tmux's buffer
    Hit <prefix>] to copy the buffer into your shell or app

vim:  wm=3
